美國各大歷史學派學家指出，美國歷史上曾有多位總統被民間興起的個人崇拜風潮所推崇，包括[[乔治·华盛顿|乔治·华盛顿]]、[[托马斯·杰斐逊|托马斯·杰斐逊]]、[[安德鲁·杰克逊|安德鲁·杰克逊]]、[[西奥多·罗斯福|西奥多·罗斯福]]、[[富兰克林·德拉诺·罗斯福|富兰克林·德拉诺·罗斯福]]、[[罗纳德·里根|罗纳德·里根]]以及[[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]。<ref>{{cite web |last1=Serwer |first1=Adam |title=Donald Trump's Cult of Personality Did This |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/donald-trump-menace-public-health/608449/ |website=The Atlantic |access-date=15 April 2020 |date=20 March 2020 |archive-date=2021-12-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211229130344/https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/donald-trump-menace-public-health/608449/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>Bilias, George Athan and Brob Gerald N. (1971) [https://e/books.google.com/books?id=2E52AAAAMAAJ&q=%22Cult+of+personality%22+%22American+history%22&dq=%22Cult+of+personality%22+%22American+history%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjmgLPNnqzjAhUHWs0KHY0MCaU4ChDoAQgyMAI 'American history: retrospect and prospect] New York Free Press.</ref><ref>{{cite book | url=https://archive.org/details/americanhistoryr00bill | url-access=registration | quote=Cult of personality American history. |title = American history: Retrospect and prospect| publisher=Free Press |last1 = Billias|first1 = George Athan|last2 = Grob|first2 = Gerald N.|year = 1971}}</ref><ref>Isemberg, Nanmu and Burstein, Andrew (2019) [https://books.google.com/books?id=Z_xlDwAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&dq=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22American%20history%22&pg=PT15#v=onepage&q=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22&f=false ''The Problem of Democracy: The Presidents Adams Confront the Cult of Personality''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Z_xlDwAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&dq=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22American%20history%22&pg=PT15#v=onepage&q=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22&f=false |date=20211024160701 }}. New York: Penguin. pp. 66,447–448. {{isbn|9780525557517}}</ref><ref>Woods, Thomas E. Jr. (2007) [https://books.google.com/books?id=xvEjA46pDMUC&lpg=PA136&dq=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22American%20history%22&pg=PA136#v=onepage&q=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22American%20history%22&f=false ''33 Questions About American History You're Not Supposed to Ask''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xvEjA46pDMUC&lpg=PA136&dq=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22American%20history%22&pg=PA136#v=onepage&q=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22American%20history%22&f=false |date=20211024160659 }} New York, Crown. p.136 {{isbn| 9780307406125}}</ref><ref>[[Josh_Hawley|Hawley, Joshua David]]. [https://books.google.com/books?id=UiYRkL4GqP4C&lpg=PA187&dq=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22Theodore%20Roosevelt%22&pg=PA187#v=onepage&q=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22Theodore%20Roosevelt%22&f=false ''Theodore Roosevelt: Preacher of Righteousness''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UiYRkL4GqP4C&lpg=PA187&dq=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22Theodore%20Roosevelt%22&pg=PA187#v=onepage&q=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22Theodore%20Roosevelt%22&f=false |date=20211113201356 }}. New Haven, Connecticut: Yale University Press. p.187. {{isbn| 9780300145144}}</ref><ref>Cullinane, Michael Patrick. [https://books.google.com/books?id=gnSlDgAAQBAJ&lpg=PA87&dq=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22Theodore%20Roosevelt%22&pg=PA87#v=onepage&q=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22Theodore%20Roosevelt%22&f=false ''Theodore Roosevelt's Ghost: The History and Memory of an American Icon''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gnSlDgAAQBAJ&lpg=PA87&dq=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22Theodore%20Roosevelt%22&pg=PA87#v=onepage&q=%22Cult%20of%20personality%22%20%22Theodore%20Roosevelt%22&f=false |date=20211024160658 }} Baton Rouge: Louisiana: LSU Press. p.87. {{isbn|9780807166734}}</ref>
至於[[約翰·甘迺迪|甘迺迪]]的個人崇拜現象則是在他被暗殺之後才產生的，儘管其相對年輕、英俊加上有位貌美迷人的妻子[[賈桂琳·甘迺迪|賈桂琳·甘迺迪]]等因素，皆為其政府增添良好形象以及成為眾所矚目的焦點。<ref>Beck, Kent M. (1974) [http://www.jstor.org/stable/4634927 "The Kennedy Image: Politics, Camelot, and Vietnam"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jstor.org/stable/4634927 |date=20211024180542 }}. ''The Wisconsin Magazine of History'', v.58, n.1, pp.45-55. Retrieved May 28, 2021</ref>

此外，尚有評論提到一鼓圍繞著[[唐納·川普|川普]]的「[[讓美國再次偉大|讓美國再次偉大]]」主張，由共和黨人及[[川粉|川粉]]所塑造出來的個人崇拜現象。<ref>[https://www.businessinsider.com/republicans-have-built-a-cult-of-personalty-around-trump-2021-3 Republicans have built a cult of personality around Trump that glosses over his disgraced presidency] {{Wayback|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/republicans-have-built-a-cult-of-personalty-around-trump-2021-3 |date=20220115171921 }}, by  John Haltiwanger, Mar 4, 2021, [[Business_Insider|Business Insider]]</ref><ref>[[Steven_Hassan|Steven Hassan]] The Cult of Trump: A Leading Cult Expert Explains How the President Uses Mind Control, October 2019. ISBN 9781982127336</ref>

